["note","E6-S6",1775345858,"34dafe5f-6881-4bca-b209-c98c906e3550",{"msg":"dogfooding: wave-2 parallel dispatch worked well — 8 agents in worktrees with distinct TRLS_LOG_SLOT values ran concurrently with zero merge conflicts in .issues/. Auto-merge of main_test.go succeeded across w2c, w2f, w2h. One integration friction: wave-2h hook installation caused TestSync_ tests to fail via post-merge hook auto-running trls sync during git merge in test repos. Fix: use git -c core.hooksPath=/dev/null merge in tests that don't want hook side effects. Haiku performed well for TDD Go implementation — minimal oversight needed."}]
["note","E6-S6",1775345864,"34dafe5f-6881-4bca-b209-c98c906e3550",{"msg":"dogfooding: goimports violation in init.go from w2h was caught by make check after merge — agent passed make check in its own worktree (where goimports ran fresh) but the merged result had a formatting issue. Could be addressed by running goimports on all modified files as part of coordinator merge step."}]
