["note","E6-S6",1775352070,"34dafe5f-6881-4bca-b209-c98c906e3550",{"msg":"dogfooding wave-3: parallel subagent bash access requires targeted allow rules in ~/.claude/settings.json (TRLS_LOG_SLOT=*, cd /tmp/trellis-w3:*, gh pr:*, env.PATH). Haiku blocked entirely in background mode; Sonnet succeeded after settings fix. w3b and w3c required coordinator handoff for git/push steps due to sandbox blocking cd to /tmp - but implementation and make check succeeded in the agents themselves. Two agents needed --force on trls transition (trls detects main branch even in worktree context)."}]
