["decision","task-1775311522",1775389515,"34dafe5f-6881-4bca-b209-c98c906e3550",{"topic":"coordinator-push vs agent-pull model","choice":"agent-pull with optional coordinator pre-assignment","rationale":"Agent-pull (worker calls trls ready and self-selects) is the correct default model for trellis. It fits the architecture better for four reasons: (1) trls ready already implements a priority-sorted, dependency-aware, claim-TTL-aware queue that is the natural intake point for any worker — the queue does the scheduling work automatically; (2) trls claim atomically marks a task and advances the parent story, so no coordinator handshake is needed to keep state consistent; (3) the SKILL doc worker loop is entirely pull-based and well-tested in practice; (4) coordinator-push (trls assign --worker X followed by agent claiming) is already supported as an overlay via OpAssign/AssignedWorker: assignment-aware sorting in ComputeReady promotes assigned tasks to the top of a specific worker's queue, giving the coordinator soft control without breaking the pull model. The gaps identified: (a) trls ready --format json does not emit the assigned_worker field, so a coordinator cannot verify pre-assignment was picked up; (b) trls ready has no --worker flag plumbing in the SKILL doc — the --worker flag exists in code but is undocumented in the worker loop skill, making the coordinator-push overlay invisible to practitioners; (c) there is no machine-readable way to ask 'which tasks are pre-assigned to worker X and still unclaimed' without grepping the index directly — a trls workers or trls ready --assigned-to X query would close this gap. Recommendation: keep agent-pull as the primary model; document the assign/unassign overlay in the SKILL; file UX gaps as follow-on tasks."}]
["create","task-1775389519",1775389519,"34dafe5f-6881-4bca-b209-c98c906e3550",{"title":"trls ready --format json should include assigned_worker field","parent":"E6","type":"task","scope":["internal/ready/compute.go","cmd/trellis/ready.go"],"definition_of_done":"ReadyEntry JSON output includes assigned_worker string field (empty string when unassigned); coordinator can verify pre-assignment was picked up by inspecting JSON output"}]
