["transition","task-1775311522",1775389543,"34dafe5f-6881-4bca-b209-c98c906e3550",{"to":"done","outcome":"Recommendation: agent-pull is the correct primary model. trls ready + trls claim already implement a priority-sorted, dependency-aware, atomic-claim queue that makes coordinator-push unnecessary for default usage. The existing assign/unassign overlay (OpAssign / AssignedWorker / assignment-aware ComputeReady sort) provides soft coordinator control without breaking pull semantics. Three UX gaps filed: task-1775389519 (ready JSON missing assigned_worker field), task-1775389525 (SKILL doc missing --worker flag and assign overlay docs), task-1775389531 (no --assigned-to filter for coordinator visibility)."}]
